# story.word — what a STORY is: all its histories, the whole told from its root.
# A story is told from a root, not given as a world is (11.md). It bottoms out in the host
# (seed/storyIdentity.js — the storyId is I_AM's key id; seed/past/fact/chainRoots.js — the
# storyRoot, a hash over the history roots). Descends from word.word, base.word, chain.word,
# history.word; every word grounded (story, history, fact, chain, hash, main). A history is one
# line of the story; the story is all of them. The storyId and its seal's signing wait for `name`.

A story is all of its histories.
Every fact is in it, on some chain, on some history.
A story has a hash over its histories. The seal binds all of it, and no other story makes it.
A story lasts. Its facts do not pass. A history branches within it, never beyond it.
The main is the first history of a story. Every other history branches from one already in it.
